{"name": "meguro", "name#zh": "\u76ee\u9ed1", "name#ja": "\u76ee\u9ed2", "repo": "typlog/meguro", "version": "0.2.1", "author": "Typlog", "images": ["https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/290496/137299261-e56658ae-29af-4b7d-a3ac-ce4aa348c915.png"], "features": {"post": true, "audio": false}, "avatar": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26949884?v=4", "stars": 0, "readme": "<div id=\"readme\" class=\"md\" data-path=\"README.md\"><article class=\"markdown-body entry-content container-lg\" itemprop=\"text\"><h1>Meguro</h1>\n<p>A Typlog theme for changelog.</p>\n<h2>Tag color</h2>\n<p>Meguro theme has 3 built-in colors for \"New\", \"Update\" and \"Fix\":</p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/290496/132989103-e072bdff-f5ad-478f-8e7a-62b31749013e.png\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/290496/132989103-e072bdff-f5ad-478f-8e7a-62b31749013e.png\" width=\"420\" alt=\"default tag colors\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"></a></p>\n<p>This happens when you define the tags slugs as: <code>new</code>, <code>update</code> and <code>fix</code>.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>It is also possible to define the tag color with <code>metadata.color</code>:</p>\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/290496/132988909-5164d6a4-29a1-45d8-9489-f1d95038e72d.png\"><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/290496/132988909-5164d6a4-29a1-45d8-9489-f1d95038e72d.png\" width=\"360\" alt=\"customize tag color\" style=\"max-width: 100%;\"></a></p>\n</article></div>"}